main event: A military report from Project Blue Book detailing a sighting of a round white object interpreted as a satellite in Kokomo, Indiana on March 17, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for 5 minutes, The object appeared white like a star and was the size of a pea, It was initially seen at an elevation of 75 degrees and disappeared at 30 degrees, The object's movement included steady northward motion followed by rapid lateral corrections, The conclusion of the investigation identified the object as ECHO II satellite due to atmospheric conditions.
sighted object: a round white object resembling a star
